Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "the data values for alcohol consumption per capita are meaningless without \
the time interval (weekly, monthly, yearly...) [see ",
 ButtonBox["Link ",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.thesun.co.uk/money/10251636/worlds-biggest-wine-lovers-\
revealed/"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://www.thesun.co.uk/money/10251636/worlds-biggest-wine-lovers-\
revealed/"],
 "and ",
 ButtonBox["Wikipedia",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_alcohol_\
consumption_per_capita"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_alcohol_consumption_\
per_capita"],
 "]. Assuming the numbers presented are yearly, they do not match with any \
rescaling that I could think of to real data. There seems to be a factor of \
x10 in need.  "
}], "Item",
