Cell["\<\
Aimed at finding a reduced representation of the dataset that produces the \
same or similar analytical results\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808638370280634*^9, 3.80863837459636*^9}},
 FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"434b6cfa-8580-427d-9dad-3e111117bb15"],

Cell["\<\
If analysis is to understand impact of drinking in Liver deaths, only, we \
might want to eliminate the attribute Heart.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808638527874737*^9, 
  3.808638602436944*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"864d4a3f-b802-4bb0-acf3-\
7b2feb49fc1e"],

Cell["\<\
If we aim at reducing storage, we could simply reduce the number of digits of \
the attributes alcohol and liver: \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808638527874737*^9, 
  3.808638636802706*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b3a64f5c-dadb-40bf-8f96-\
8495e8455774"],

Cell["\<\
Reduce to 2 digits values of attribute \"Alcohol\" (see bellow a standard \
computing approach to take more significant digits)\
\>", "Text",
